<text top="332" left="185" width="473" height="23" font="6"><b>Official communiqué of the 5042nd (closed) meeting</b></text>
<text top="355" left="185" width="208" height="23" font="6"><b>of the Security Council</b></text>
<text top="396" left="185" width="472" height="20" font="7"><b>Held in private at Headquarters, New York, on Thursday,</b></text>
<text top="417" left="185" width="260" height="20" font="7"><b>23 September 2004, at 3.30 p.m.</b></text>
<text top="456" left="220" width="513" height="17" font="2">In accordance with rule 55 of the provisional rules of procedure of the Security</text>
<text top="474" left="185" width="548" height="17" font="2">Council, the following communiqué was issued through the Secretary-General in</text>
<text top="492" left="185" width="174" height="17" font="2">place of a verbatim record:</text>
<text top="519" left="256" width="477" height="17" font="2">"At its 5042nd meeting, held in private on 23 September 2004, the</text>
<text top="537" left="220" width="470" height="17" font="2">Security Council considered the item entitled `The situation in Burundi'.</text>
<text top="564" left="256" width="477" height="17" font="2">"His Excellency Mr. Domitien Ndayizeye, the distinguished President of</text>
<text top="582" left="220" width="513" height="17" font="2">the Republic of Burundi, was invited, in response to his request, to participate</text>
<text top="600" left="220" width="513" height="17" font="2">in the discussion, in accordance with rule 37 of the Council's provisional rules</text>
<text top="618" left="220" width="86" height="17" font="2">of procedure.</text>
<text top="645" left="256" width="477" height="17" font="2">"The Security Council heard a briefing by His Excellency Mr. Domitien</text>
<text top="663" left="220" width="73" height="17" font="2">Ndayizeye.</text>
<text top="690" left="256" width="477" height="17" font="2">"Members of the Council and President Ndayizeye had a constructive</text>
<text top="708" left="220" width="131" height="17" font="2">exchange of views."</text>
</page>
